                  <div class="small text-muted">
                    Simulates a realistic <strong>Event ID 9999 High CPU Alert</strong> by writing
                    a real Windows Event Log entry, injecting it into the dashboard pipeline,
                    and triggering a one-click remediation — all from the live alert pop-up.
                  </div>

                  <!-- Step 1 -->
                  <div class="p-3 rounded" style="background:rgba(255,78,80,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(255,78,80,0.3);">
                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                      <span class="badge bg-danger">Step 1</span>
                      <strong class="small">Inject the Error</strong>
                    </div>
                    <div class="small text-muted mb-2">
                      Writes Event ID 9999 to Windows Application Log and registers it
                      in the dashboard database. The <strong>live alert pop-up</strong> will
                      appear on the Dashboard within 5 seconds.
                    </div>
                    <button class="btn btn-danger btn-modern w-100" id="highcpu-inject-btn" onclick="injectHighCpuAlertFromSim()">
                      <i class="fas fa-bolt me-1"></i>Inject High CPU Error
                    </button>
                  </div>

                  <!-- Step 2 -->
                  <div class="p-3 rounded" style="background:rgba(40,167,69,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(40,167,69,0.25);">
                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                      <span class="badge bg-success">Step 2</span>
                      <strong class="small">Remediate from Pop-up</strong>
                    </div>
                    <div class="small text-muted">
                      After the alert appears, click <strong>"Auto-Remediate Now"</strong> in the
                      pop-up on the Dashboard tab. This runs <code>Remediate_HighCpuAlert.ps1</code>
                      and marks the incident as resolved.
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="small">
                    <div class="mb-1"><strong>Inject Script:</strong> <code>Simulate_HighCpuAlert.ps1</code></div>
                    <div><strong>Remediation Script:</strong> <code>Remediate_HighCpuAlert.ps1</code></div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="alert alert-info mb-0 small" id="highcpu-sim-status-box">
                    <i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i>Ready. Click "Inject High CPU Error" to begin.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

